<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="shell">
      <section class="hero">
        <span class="eyebrow">Case Study Domain</span>
        <h1>Telemedicine Prescription Management</h1>
        <p>
          Search prescription records using Prescription ID and Patient ID, review the full record,
          and update only the allowed fields when the prescription status is still open.
        </p>
        <div class="card-strip">
          <div class="mini-card">
            <strong>Search Inputs</strong>
            <p>Prescription ID and Patient ID are both required before loading a record.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mini-card">
            <strong>Editable Fields</strong>
            <p>Follow-up date, pharmacy preference, and dosage instructions can be changed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mini-card">
            <strong>Business Rule</strong>
            <p>Records can be updated only if the prescription status remains <strong>OPEN</strong>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="button" href="/prescriptions/search">Open Search Form</a>
          <% if (lastViewedId) { %>
            <span class="hint">Last viewed prescription: <strong><%= lastViewedId %></strong></span>
          <% } %>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="panel">
        <h2>Expected Workflow</h2>
        <div class="grid">
          <div class="mini-card">
            <strong>1. Validate</strong>
            <p>Client-side and server-side validation check both identifiers before searching.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mini-card">
            <strong>2. Display</strong>
            <p>The app shows the complete prescription record only when it exists.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mini-card">
            <strong>3. Update</strong>
            <p>Only selected fields are editable and the status rule is enforced before save.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mini-card">
            <strong>4. Result</strong>
            <p>A dedicated success or failure page is shown after each action.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
